<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 4:49PM CDT  by NWS Memphis</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Cross
County through 515 PM CDT...
At 449 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cherry Valley, or 8 miles northwest of Parkin, moving southwest at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Coldwater, Colton, Twist, Togo and Birdeye.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
